while managing the team

881
00:49:47,567 --> 00:49:49,111
through thick and thin.

882
00:49:50,904 --> 00:49:52,322
Will you go out for a drink?

883
00:49:54,032 --> 00:49:56,118
I do want to get close to you,

884
00:49:56,201 --> 00:49:58,370
but I don't think I should
at the same time.

885
00:49:58,453 --> 00:49:59,788
What is this feeling?

886
00:49:59,871 --> 00:50:02,958
I also want to get close,
but I don't think I should.

887
00:50:03,542 --> 00:50:05,293
So I decline your offer.

888
00:50:05,377 --> 00:50:06,461
Gosh.

889
00:50:07,629 --> 00:50:10,465
Mr. Baek, you're really charming.

890
00:50:15,137 --> 00:50:16,346
We'll shake hands then.

891
00:50:22,060 --> 00:50:24,396
I've been telling numerous players

892
00:50:24,479 --> 00:50:27,107
that their time as athletes is over
until now.

893
00:50:28,358 --> 00:50:30,360
It's something I could also hear
at any time.

894
00:50:30,444 --> 00:50:32,112
I thought...

895
00:50:33,572 --> 00:50:35,574
you could stay
if the parent company changed.

896
00:50:36,241 --> 00:50:37,451
I'm okay.

897
00:50:38,034 --> 00:50:39,578
Should I try to persuade them again?

898
00:50:39,661 --> 00:50:41,663
No, he's busy.

899
00:50:42,706 --> 00:50:44,916
And he's yielded so many things already.

900
00:51:01,475 --> 00:51:02,517
It's over there.

901
00:51:03,310 --> 00:51:04,269
I'm sure of it.

902
00:51:06,938 --> 00:51:09,191
My dad often worked at construction sites,

903
00:51:10,484 --> 00:51:12,360
but he didn't get paid for his work.

904
00:51:13,737 --> 00:51:15,906
My mom was always frustrated.

905
00:51:17,616 --> 00:51:19,993
But he said those people
had their reasons.

906
00:51:21,870 --> 00:51:23,580
He just smoked cigarettes

907
00:51:24,456 --> 00:51:25,999
and struggled inside.

908
00:51:28,168 --> 00:51:30,128
But when he got money somehow,

909
00:51:31,379 --> 00:51:32,631
he came to a ballpark

910
00:51:33,715 --> 00:51:34,925
with me.

911
00:51:36,301 --> 00:51:37,552
My mom wouldn't come,

912
00:51:38,220 --> 00:51:39,596
so he dragged me instead.

913
00:51:41,264 --> 00:51:42,516
But that day,

914
00:51:43,600 --> 00:51:45,852
maybe he was really short on money.

915
00:51:47,229 --> 00:51:49,981
He didn't buy me hotteok at the ballpark

916
00:51:50,690 --> 00:51:51,691
unlike usually.

917
00:51:52,943 --> 00:51:55,070
He watched the game speechlessly.

918
00:51:58,031 --> 00:52:01,451
I didn't even get to ask him
for some hotteok.

919
00:52:03,370 --> 00:52:06,581
The Dreams were
on their seventh defeat in a row.

920
00:52:07,332 --> 00:52:09,167
But of all pitchers, the Titans sent

921
00:52:09,709 --> 00:52:11,753
Choi Soo-won,
the most-wanted national athlete,

922
00:52:12,379 --> 00:52:15,215
who was like Kang Doo-ki now.

923
00:52:18,635 --> 00:52:19,928
All the teams

924
00:52:20,428 --> 00:52:22,639
wanted to take three wins
against the Dreams,

925
00:52:23,598 --> 00:52:26,226
so they sent good pitchers

926
00:52:26,309 --> 00:52:27,727
on the mound.

927
00:52:28,311 --> 00:52:31,439
It's cowardly to defeat
a weak team completely,

928
00:52:31,523 --> 00:52:33,191
but it's an effective way.

929
00:52:33,900 --> 00:52:35,443
Some men were yelling

930
00:52:35,527 --> 00:52:38,697
to fire the manager.

931
00:52:40,657 --> 00:52:41,741
It was a mess.

932
00:52:43,577 --> 00:52:44,536
But then,

933
00:52:45,161 --> 00:52:46,538
Um Sang Gu...

934
00:52:47,747 --> 00:52:49,624
hit a home run worth three points.

935
00:52:52,127 --> 00:52:54,629
Those middle-aged men who were shouting,

936
00:52:54,713 --> 00:52:56,089
my dad,

937
00:52:56,172 --> 00:52:57,757
and everyone jumped up and down

938
00:52:58,550 --> 00:53:00,677
because of that one home run.

939
00:53:03,722 --> 00:53:04,764
They cried...

940
00:53:06,474 --> 00:53:07,726
as grownups.

941
00:53:10,562 --> 00:53:11,980
It was a nice match.

942
00:53:12,606 --> 00:53:14,232
The next day,

943
00:53:14,733 --> 00:53:17,068
my dad went to his boss
who didn't pay him.

944
00:53:18,069 --> 00:53:19,571
He grabbed him by the collar.

945
00:53:20,614 --> 00:53:22,699
So did he get paid?

946
00:53:23,909 --> 00:53:25,744
I'm not sure,

947
00:53:26,453 --> 00:53:28,413
but I guess he didn't get the full amount.

948
00:53:28,496 --> 00:53:31,082
I remember having braised tofu
for dinner that day.

949
00:53:32,125 --> 00:53:34,169
You even remember the side dish?

950
00:53:35,545 --> 00:53:36,546
Anyway...

951
00:53:38,340 --> 00:53:40,717
I went to a ballpark again with my dad.

952
00:53:40,800 --> 00:53:43,470
I ate hotteok during the game that day.

953
00:53:45,221 --> 00:53:46,222
Sometimes

954
00:53:47,182 --> 00:53:49,601
when it's hard working
for the backmarker team...

955
00:53:51,478 --> 00:53:53,855
I look at that seat at the ballpark.

956
00:53:55,440 --> 00:53:56,733
It becomes bearable then.

957
00:53:58,360 --> 00:53:59,402
You've protected

958
00:54:00,236 --> 00:54:02,530
such a place.

959
00:54:07,410 --> 00:54:08,578
Won't there be any way

960
00:54:09,829 --> 00:54:11,456
for you to stay?

961
00:54:12,707 --> 00:54:15,835
I'm used to leaving like this.

962
00:54:17,754 --> 00:54:20,715
It's the first time in my career
that my team will exist

963
00:54:21,549 --> 00:54:23,468
even after I leave.

964
00:54:26,054 --> 00:54:27,097
No one...

965
00:54:29,891 --> 00:54:32,310
got to protect you this time either.

966
00:54:34,312 --> 00:54:35,897
No, for me,

967
00:54:36,481 --> 00:54:40,360
I'll remember it as a team
that I protected for the first time.

968
00:54:43,113 --> 00:54:44,197
This will...

969
00:54:52,872 --> 00:54:53,957
give me...

970
00:54:55,834 --> 00:54:57,252
