01:00:30,877 --> 01:00:33,921
Lim Dong-gyu hits the ball,
and it goes high toward the center.

1046
01:00:34,005 --> 01:00:34,881
High!

1047
01:00:34,964 --> 01:00:37,133
-High!
-It went over.

1048
01:00:37,216 --> 01:00:39,260
-It's a home run.
-It went over the fence!

1049
01:00:39,344 --> 01:00:41,095
He hits a home run
and marks the first score.

1050
01:00:41,179 --> 01:00:42,680
He's impressive.

1051
01:00:42,764 --> 01:00:44,849
I can tell he's determined

1052
01:00:44,932 --> 01:00:47,018
not to let the Sabers seize this fall.

1053
01:01:03,451 --> 01:01:04,827
Are you going to be there on time?

1054
01:01:06,037 --> 01:01:08,623
-Yes.
-I told them that you're very rude,

1055
01:01:08,706 --> 01:01:11,000
but good at work.

1056
01:01:11,084 --> 01:01:12,043
They liked it.

1057
01:01:12,126 --> 01:01:15,797
They might prefer someone who's only
good at work. What a shame for them.

1058
01:01:16,422 --> 01:01:17,340
Mr. Baek.

1059
01:01:18,257 --> 01:01:19,092
Yes?

1060
01:01:19,592 --> 01:01:23,805
Are you sure you can do it?
You barely got used to baseball.

1061
01:01:23,888 --> 01:01:25,056
But another sport?

1062
01:01:25,682 --> 01:01:28,935
I'm not sure.
I might have to give it a go,

1063
01:01:29,018 --> 01:01:30,395
but I'll do my best.

1064
01:01:33,314 --> 01:01:34,315
Isn't it the same...

1065
01:01:35,900 --> 01:01:37,026
for everyone?

1066
01:01:54,752 --> 01:01:58,840
You may not be strong, but it's okay
because we'll help each other.

1067
01:01:58,923 --> 01:02:01,175
SPECIAL THANKS TO LEE JE-HOON, PENGSOO,

1068
01:02:01,259 --> 01:02:03,261
LEE SOON-CHEOL, AND JEONG WOO-YOUNG

1069
01:03:00,610 --> 01:03:03,571
THANKS FOR WATCHING.
